Round 2 of the 2018 WGC – Mexico Championship golf tournament will be played on Friday 2nd March at the Chapultepec Golf Club in Mexico City, Mexico. The WGC – Mexico Championship 2nd round tee times have been announced and the round is scheduled to start at 11:15 am. Players will remain in the same groups as the 1st round but alternate between AM/PM sessions and 1st tee/10th tee starts depending on their 1st round tee times. The 2018 WGC – Mexico Championship round 2 tee times and player pairings. All tee times are displayed local time. Groups starting from the 1st hole are listed first, followed by groups starting from the 10th hole.  The post WGC – Mexico Championship 2018 Round 2 Tee Times & Player Pairings appeared first on Golf and Course. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from News – Golf and Course. Click here to read the full text on the original website.